An investigation has been launched after a group of prison officers went on a night out wearing T-shirts with the words 'We have Madeleine McCann' printed on them.

One of the officers has been sacked and four others disciplined after photos of them wearing the T-shirts were posted online, it has been reported.

The pictures were on Facebook for two months before bosses at Wandsworth Prison, in south London, were alerted.

