According to the Metro, the incident led to a prison officer being sacked and four others disciplined.

But a member of staff at the prison told the paper there were some officers who had been involved in the incident but were still working at the prison.

He said: ‘It makes me sick to think just because they work for the prison service that they should get away with this disrespectful behaviour.'

It is a disciplinary offence for officers to bring the prison service into disrepute through social media, according to their code of conduct.

A Prison Service spokesman told MailOnline: 'An investigation has taken place at HMP Wandsworth and appropriate disciplinary action has been taken following an incident concerning a number of prison officers outside of working hours and away from the prison.

'Until the disciplinary process is completed we are unable to comment further.'

